    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** stands out as the clear offensive engine for Ghost Ride the WHIP with an elite efficiency score of 79.74. While he faces Pop, his combination of a prime #2 lineup spot and favorable wind conditions provides the highest ceiling on the board; the 7% boost from the matchup against an SP with a 4.28 xERA makes him an auto-start despite the minor hurdle of an elite defensive catcher. Similarly, **Josh Naylor** (68.46) and **Brice Turang** (67.73) provide high-floor production, with **Turang** benefiting significantly from a 10% bump for leading off against Littell. **Trevor Story** (65.90) is an interesting play today, as his favorable matchup against Pallante is amplified by the pitcher\u2019s slow delivery, which projects to pay dividends in our quest for stolen bases.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was **Zach McKinstry**, who narrowly missed the cut with a 50.08 score. While his 97% stolen base opportunity against Alcantara was tantalizing, the combination of a #8 lineup spot and the overall high efficiency of our projected starters relegated him to the pine. We are also keeping a close eye on **Mickey Moniak** (65.20); while his matchup against Pivetta is strong, the 39% rain risk creates a volatility flag that could necessitate a pivot if the game is delayed or postponed. Meanwhile, **Dalton Rushing** is our lowest-rated starter at 40.55, primarily due to the daunting task of facing deGrom. While his platoon edge provides a slight buffer, he remains a candidate for a late-game substitution if his early at-bats prove unproductive.",
